{
  "texts": [
    "According to Table 3, OTR, which is based on the CF framework without deep features, achieves the best performance among all competitors.",
    "The reason for the promising result is that 3D construction provides a useful constraint for filter learning.",
    "The same conclusion is obtained for CA3DMS and 3DT, which construct a 3D model to locate the target via mean-shift and sparse learning methods.",
    "These trackers with traditional features are competitive with deep trackers.",
    "DL-based trackers (WCO, TACF, and CSR-RGBD) achieve substantial performance, indicating the successful discrimination of deep features."
  ]
}